messages.text: was robin hood a real person?

Yes, Robin Hood was indeed a real historical figure who lived in England during the medieval period (1184-1327). He was known for his outlaw status and his reputation as an excellent archer and skilled thief. Robin's exploits were legendary, and he became famous throughout Europe due to his bravery and heroism. However, there is no definitive evidence that he existed as a person other than legend or fiction. The character of Robin Hood may have been inspired by actual people and events from the time period.
